Text Data and Argument Specifiers - Exercise #2
Use the string and integer argument specifiers, along with indexing, to create the following sentence using the four variables listed below.

"The "Fast Cars" shop are expecting to sell 1000 units of the new Audi model at 37500.50 per unit next year."

car_shop = ['Fast Cars', 'Elegant Cars']
car_brand = ['Audi', 'Ford']
number_of_cars_for_sale = [1000, 1200]
price_of_model = 37500.50
Please remember to use the print() function to print out the desired output.




car_shop = ['Fast Cars', 'Elegant Cars']
car_brand = ['Audi', 'Ford']
number_of_cars_for_sale = [1000, 1200]
price_of_model = 37500.50
print("The \"%s\" shop are expecting to sell %d units of the new %s model at %.2f per unit next year."%(car_shop[0],number_of_cars_for_sale[0],car_brand[0],round(price_of_model,2)))
